basePhenomenon is the fundamental property being observerd. e.g. 'Precipitation'

Statistically significant information e.g. MAXIMUM over MONTH SUM RATE In some circumstances it may be desirable to used 'derivedFrom' to expose some level of derivation information: e.g.: MEAN over YEAR derivedFrom MEAN over MONTH Or: RATE derivedFrom SUM over HOUR However the StatisticalQualifier is not intended to be used to describe the entire data generation process. Its purpose should be limited to expressing the minimum statistical information that is essential for initial interpretation of result data.
MEAN over DECADES derivedFrom MEAN over MONTHS derivedFrom MAX over DAYS
